cboe from bill brodsky who moved to the newly created role of executive chairman with six months under his belt john lothian news publisher john lothian sat down with him to talk about his new job new initiatives from the cboe and the challenges facing the industry getting shorter cboe’s ed tilly introduces shortterm vix and industry taxes in part  of this interview tilly talks about the cboe extending the vix trading hours to access trading from european traders and how he expects the vix will someday be open the same hours as the cme’s globex sp  futures he also talked about the cboe’s new vxst shortterm vix contract which will offer traders a much more sensitive instrument to be able to trade shortterm events he spoke about the meeting the industry had with the chairman of the sec about problems that have plagued the markets in recent months lastly he spoke about the impact of the camp proposal a piece of proposed legislation from rep dave camp rmi a member of the house committee on ways  means that could have a big impact on the options business and its customers camp’s proposal includes several provisions that would change the tax treatment for strategies used in options trading some believe it could severely harm the listed options business in the united states marketswiki education videos references ↑ cboe holdings announces planned changes in board leadership roles at close of transaction with bats global markets cboe ↑ press release cboe ↑ taking the reins cboe’s ed tilly makes the transition to ceo john lothian news ↑ getting shorter cboe’s ed tilly introduces shortterm vix and industry taxes john lothian news retrieved from httpwwwmarketswikicomwikiindexphptitleedwardttillyoldid categories sponsored pagessponsored pages  cboereserved pagesreserved pages  cboecboe  current employeescboebiographiescboe executivesbios  cboecboe board membersoccocc  board membersexchange ceosmarketswiki education navigation menu personal tools log in namespaces page discussio